HEADWORD: Genially
<hw>Gen"ial*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>By
genius or nature; naturally.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some men are <qex>genially</qex> disposed to some opinions.</q>
<rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gayly; cheerfully.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Genialness</ent>⟦br⟧
